{"docstring":"The project integrates a comprehensive code quality tooling suite to enforce\nPEP 8 compliance, strict static typing, complexity thresholds, dynamic\ntest coverage, and mutation testing logic.\n\nThis ensures that the codebase remains readable, maintainable, secure, and\nfunctionally verified.","hash":"6dc6920a67d5a0ea9f35e26cbb9ea78274c82858cd57f9b4ae5955e3a6b58502","inherits":["spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Feature"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.code_quality.CodeQualitySuite","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"Coverage.py must be integrated to monitor dynamic test execution coverage.\n\nRequirements:\n1. Execution Tracking:\n   - Record which statements, lines, and branches are executed by the\n     automated test suite.\n\n2. Target Coverage:\n   - Enforce a minimum statement/line coverage threshold of 80% or higher\n     across the codebases.\n   - Fail the CI/CD pipeline if the overall test coverage falls below the\n     defined threshold.","hash":"13516c08c2b52ad0e478378ee1aaf92c0ff69c179e779f84bd5de03f684387f7","inherits":["spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.code_quality.CoverageIntegration","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"Mutmut must be integrated for mutation testing to validate test suite effectiveness.\n\nRequirements:\n1. Abstract Syntax Tree Mutation:\n   - Mutmut must actively modify the python AST to inject subtle bugs (e.g.\n     changing operators, swapping comparisons, replacing constants).\n\n2. Efficacy Verification:\n   - Prove that the unit test suite actively catches injected logical faults.\n   - Identify \"surviving mutants\" to reveal weak or missing assertions in\n     our test cases.","hash":"225e88b42597b50eb9a43731eb219c578c94e8afb6bc89365711b3a401412a86","inherits":["spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.code_quality.MutmutIntegration","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"Mypy must be integrated for strict static type checking compliance.\n\nRequirements:\n1. Static Typing Verification:\n   - Validate all type hints and signatures across the source, spec, and\n     test codebases to ensure data consistency and prevent runtime bugs.\n\n2. Python 3.12 Compatibility:\n   - Ensure Mypy is configured to target Python 3.12 features, such as\n     PEP 695 type statement, generic type aliases, and PEP 698 override\n     decorator.\n\n3. Enforce Strict Mode:\n   - Configure type checking options (e.g., disallowing untyped calls or\n     def definitions) to maintain high strictness across modules.","hash":"f183e1dfdea43a2b0e456125a8e88110349491671c9578271bda4ecc4156138d","inherits":["spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.code_quality.MypyIntegration","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"Radon must be integrated to measure cyclomatic complexity and code maintainability.\n\nRequirements:\n1. Complexity Thresholds:\n   - Compute cyclomatic complexity (CC) scores for all functions and\n     methods.\n   - Flag any function with a complexity score above 10 for refactoring\n     to prevent error-prone code paths.\n\n2. Maintainability Index (MI):\n   - Calculate Halstead volume and lines of code (LOC) to assign a\n     maintainability index score (from A to F).\n   - Maintain a target of Grade A or B for all modules.","hash":"ac9c9fa952430aab833f69c82da3feaf1d00ae323b43ce96a81e6bb2bfebf847","inherits":["spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.code_quality.RadonIntegration","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"Ruff must be integrated as the primary linter and formatter.\n\nRequirements:\n1. Syntax and Style Compliance:\n   - Instantly flag PEP 8 styling errors, unused imports, and common code\n     smells using Ruff.\n   - Enforce consistent code formatting (using `ruff format`).\n\n2. Python 3.12 Compatibility:\n   - Ensure Ruff is configured to support Python 3.12 syntax and rules,\n     including new f-string parsing, type parameter syntax (PEP 695),\n     and generic classes/functions.\n\n3. CLI and CI/CD Execution:\n   - The tool must run locally and in CI/CD pipelines to block commits with\n     styling or linting failures.","hash":"c9cdac117858709cb765c1394921581038257571b3a2048785a27ab5e5658380","inherits":["spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.code_quality.RuffIntegration","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"Astral's `uv` must be adopted as the unified package, dependency, and environment manager.\n\nRequirements:\n1. Dependency Locking and Reproducibility:\n   - Generate cross-platform `uv.lock` files that capture resolutions for all\n     platforms.\n   - Ensure consistent and reproducible environments across developer setups\n     and CI/CD pipelines.\n\n2. Tool Execution and Ephemeral Environments:\n   - Support ephemeral tool execution (via `uvx` or `uv run`) to run code\n     quality tools (Ruff, Mypy, Radon, Coverage, Mutmut) without polluting\n     the core project virtual environment.\n\n3. Disk Space and Installation Optimization:\n   - Leverage `uv`'s global content-addressable cache and hardlink support\n     for near-instantaneous environment builds and space efficiency.","hash":"89fdd909e893d9a2deb108303d27103e93e926c6bfe01a136cfaaa273b719533","inherits":["spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.code_quality.UvPackageManager","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"If you can see a way to reduce boiler plate, then do it.","hash":"4c72c13e4d23792d2025b09c5e068526c8297d31e97c8246066ec51a5b49ca22","inherits":[],"is_dependency":true,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.err.BoilerPlate","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"It is important that error handling be done excellently.\n\nIf a function can fail, then it needs to do so in the most elegant way\npossible. Error reporting, handling, exceptions and all aspects of failure\nmust be taken to extreme. It should be possible to understand the program\nby reading the error messages.\n\nWhen an error occurs there should be a story about the failure at each step\nof the way. What went wrong and why.","hash":"0e96c48c01cacaa890ae956a16ca1116cef5d440dfb12e64eb5a2ff08950ddea","inherits":[],"is_dependency":true,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.err.Err","type":"component"}
