{"docstring":"Before a function returns, it should verify postconditions to ensure\ninvariant properties hold true.\n\nRaise explicit, descriptive exceptions (such as RuntimeError or domain\nexceptions) rather than using `assert` statements to handle post-execution\nverification failures.","hash":"279c74d9528c72ee6280a11b16e88313fdda1e8353ed8e87f03364285a40a198","inherits":[],"is_dependency":true,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.err.PostCondition","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"Functions should validate preconditions at their entry point.\n\nInstead of using `assert` statements (which can be disabled globally),\nraise explicit, descriptive exceptions (e.g., ValueError, TypeError, or\ncustom domain exceptions) to robustly reject malformed input.","hash":"ab9cc3e3ece46db3e1a90eee8fc51cb0426a9d4a213fc30cd2879cd023d7febf","inherits":[],"is_dependency":true,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.err.PreCondition","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"Always keep an eye out for ways to generalize a function if it's utility\nmight be helpful to other functions.\n\nClasses should be implemented in their own files with filename being the\nclassname with correct naming convention","hash":"682100038b469d345d59103e4478ad85a7e1e8b22973d02345b73a1f8f38644d","inherits":["spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation"],"is_dependency":true,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.err.Refactor","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"Always prioritize library-provided constructors for complex objects. Ensure\nall components are fully initialized before calling any state- mutating\nmethods. Assume private internal state is uninitialized until the official\nconstructor has returned. When extending library components, prioritize\ncomposition (pointers) over embedding by value to avoid risky state-copying\nbugs.\n\nUse dependency injection for system level objects for composability and to\nmake testing easier.","hash":"fc789727dc39d1592ac6757f5f421e84b69b5af906f47407232650ef2ad24697","inherits":["spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState"],"is_dependency":true,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.err.Robustness","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"The supervised training phase must complete within 50 epochs or when\nvalidation accuracy exceeds 95% to allow adequate convergence.\n\nThe REINFORCE fine-tuning phase must run for at least 300 episodes to\nprovide sufficient exploration for the reward signal to shape behaviour\nbeyond what the behavioral cloning phase achieves.","hash":"7ee4b2ffb6e5cfc16a8ba0de77ce9436cfcc8fda3cab9558f3b66cff809c978f","inherits":["spec.rltree.BehavioralCloningBootstrap","spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.BcExecutionLimit","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"Supervised learning must optimize cross-entropy loss using the Adam optimizer\nwith a standard learning rate (e.g., 1e-3).\n\nThe loss must use inverse-frequency class weighting so that the dominant\n`close_node` action — which appears once per node and skews the label\ndistribution — does not overwhelm the gradient signal for rarer add-child actions.","hash":"11f05686ffb8d7149d70facf3cbca33d3d9e1dfdaf13602e11b758fd3ff5a1d6","inherits":["spec.rltree.BehavioralCloningBootstrap","spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.BcLossAndOptimizer","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"Supervised training must run over the extracted state-action pairs, tracking\nboth training loss and validation accuracy.","hash":"3ac1ea5d602eb87a90d37e7c9a75548d8bf378bc6e7559914d92b7cf3b5c0feb","inherits":["spec.rltree.BehavioralCloningBootstrap","spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.BcTrainingLoop","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"The training process must begin with a behavioral cloning phase.\n\nThe model must first be trained using supervised learning on the synthetic\nground-truth pairs to quickly establish basic syntactic and structural\ncompetence before transitioning to reinforcement learning.","hash":"42f3b5e2deecc50dda7e0f5347678bdf028ae1d68f31636fc2ee406fc5611562","inherits":["spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.BehavioralCloningBootstrap","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"The model must be fine-tuned using REINFORCE with dense rewards.\n\nThe agent must receive immediate feedback after every action:\n- Positive reward (+1) for structurally valid moves and schema adherence.\n- Negative reward (-1) for invalid operations.\n- Termination bonus (+5) for completing a valid tree.","hash":"7ed55d4366e87e0f45941c39c27c17bc3284b56b7dca68af52b2504b431fde38","inherits":["spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.DenseReinforceFineTuning","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"The parser must perform a depth-first search (DFS) traversal of the element tree,\nrecording state contexts and target actions at each node entry and exit.","hash":"c18f6f768d043f0b6bd3004f455c5b9298569de48cc9c2e88cb93d1d8b4d08f5","inherits":["spec.rltree.DfsTupleExtraction","spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.DfsTraversal","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"The system must translate parsed trees into localized state-action pairs.\n\nFor every node visit and closure during a DFS traversal, the pipeline must\nextract the tuple: (Depth, Parent_Tag, Current_Tag, Sibling_Index, Total_Siblings)\nmapped to the corresponding tree operation (add_child or close_node).","hash":"d4220ba01e27261f37395f780b4b0d947b514fe9bef315f42b761306417b11ce","inherits":["spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.DfsTupleExtraction","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"The entire pipeline must execute in under 3 minutes.\n\nThis includes data generation, behavioral cloning, RL fine-tuning, and\na sample inference run that outputs a valid SVG string.","hash":"239dcb37ab58eadb37aaf5d27f20ac63bc47d596925f1c489b276a18c9c323f7","inherits":["spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.ExecutionTimeConstraint","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"The policy model must be a lightweight Multi-Layer Perceptron (MLP).\n\nTo meet the time constraints, the model should utilize small embedding\nlayers for categorical inputs and no more than two hidden layers of 64\nunits each.","hash":"19e4690d4617d9dd8b587c13bb258bc1a3ad0e05eabe4e895b2009c737903d96","inherits":["spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.MinimalPytorchMlp","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"The model must use discrete embedding layers for categorical variables\nsuch as `Parent_Tag_Id` and `Current_Tag_Id`.","hash":"e5403597e4cc5333923f20de76507d5bf411cfce36d448ee23d639819e34b687","inherits":["spec.rltree.MinimalPytorchMlp","spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.MlpEmbeddingLayers","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"The policy network must have exactly two hidden fully connected layers\nof 64 hidden units each, utilizing ReLU activations.","hash":"eea134ed0cec1c89ab39e77f872b34c20e0ae2176cce30158e42c6495149e827","inherits":["spec.rltree.MinimalPytorchMlp","spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.MlpHiddenLayers","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"The policy network output layer must produce a probability distribution\nover the action space using a Softmax activation.","hash":"70807c13635d36b9751dae2f313c9feed09c1cf50f7a4167f05341593936b92b","inherits":["spec.rltree.MinimalPytorchMlp","spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.MlpOutputDistribution","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"The state representation must encode the current tree node context as a\nnumeric tuple: (Depth, Parent_Tag_Id, Current_Tag_Id, Sibling_Index, Total_Siblings).","hash":"e609f8eb308ce742a499de467951c6c974b076d6c596575c6ff1c5fc9ec17c8c","inherits":["spec.rltree.DfsTupleExtraction","spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.ObservationStateEncoder","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"Rapid Proof-of-Concept for rltree.\n\nThe goal is to demonstrate a functional RL-driven tree generation pipeline\nthat completes training and evaluation in under 3 minutes on local hardware.","hash":"409f3e222ec5e6fb2e7dd329e5ead4f30b0c551b22fd2f60ad92794d892caf8d","inherits":["spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Feature"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.RapidPoC","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"The agent must interact with a step-by-step tree-building environment that\nmaintains a pointer to the active node and exposes `reset()` and `step(action)` methods.","hash":"da1b04fbdae3eca54dd7d74173300f8f4fd3fcaf8c6c2c784ababe9d8ce6b7c6","inherits":["spec.rltree.DenseReinforceFineTuning","spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.RlEnvironment","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"The policy network must be fine-tuned using the REINFORCE algorithm to optimize\nthe cumulative reward over trajectories of maximum length 15.","hash":"25a36810e6ac707abce7a3005b2ec8c4cc4c4cbb6b11bf0964e6621509a03b06","inherits":["spec.rltree.DenseReinforceFineTuning","spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.RlPolicyGradient","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"The environment's reward function must prevent mode collapse by ensuring\nthe agent cannot exploit a trivial shortcut of immediately closing the root.\n\nConcretely, the reward function must:\n- +0.1 for a structurally valid child-add move.\n- +1.0 schema bonus if the parent-child tag pair is present in the training set.\n- -1.0 penalty for invalid child-add actions (e.g., exceeding max depth/nodes,\n  or attempting to add a duplicate root).\n- -3.0 penalty for closing the root when it has no children (empty tree shortcut).\n- +5.0 + 0.5 * (node_count - 1) bonus for successfully closing the root with\n  at least one child, scaling incentive with tree richness.","hash":"68b7f137ccc81479142526e3b18f89176aed4a784981779a78e552749a08898b","inherits":["spec.rltree.DenseReinforceFineTuning","spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.RlRewardFunction","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"The dataset generator must produce 50 to 100 training SVGs and a separate,\nheld-out validation set of 10 to 20 SVGs.","hash":"e5bf8079a7a9279e0c6224e04a6c0096eba861e7a2273645e7acefda85f9fa73","inherits":["spec.rltree.SyntheticSvgDataset","spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.SvgDatasetSize","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"Generated SVG trees must have at most 6 nodes and a maximum depth of 3 to\nprevent scaling issues during rapid proof-of-concept development.","hash":"ff960327f6420f4b00bfa349952927e3910a13ac2a80d894c9f7224c03d587be","inherits":["spec.rltree.SyntheticSvgDataset","spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.SvgNodeAndDepthLimits","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"The SVG generation vocabulary must be strictly restricted to a small set of tags:\n['svg', 'g', 'rect', 'circle', 'path'].","hash":"17630317df3ff136db1f73bb21c5d1ce2fc7de900f7d3cf652c165f1373f7487","inherits":["spec.rltree.SyntheticSvgDataset","spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.SvgTagVocabulary","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"The pipeline must parse SVGs using standard Python `xml.etree.ElementTree`\nto guarantee well-formed input structures.","hash":"edcb4a97602ad7fa8516b8af0f926bbfbe80910f052ff5143b3a854cc10d6a80","inherits":["spec.rltree.DfsTupleExtraction","spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.SvgXmlParser","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"The system must generate a tiny synthetic dataset of valid SVGs.\n\nTo ensure rapid training, the dataset should consist of 50-100 SVGs with\na maximum of 6 nodes and a maximum depth of 3 (e.g., <svg><g><circle/></g></svg>).","hash":"80f7e3e704ced89175437f5939fbb526ec40b7662c3fdc0f170dbb6b645c66e6","inherits":["spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.SyntheticSvgDataset","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"The action labels must be encoded as discrete integers corresponding to:\n- `add_child(tag_id)` for each tag in the vocabulary\n- `close_node`","hash":"8f0cdf4339d1b315f407dd30ed490b379ce82aa46d63eb18b7806a792e6f9265","inherits":["spec.rltree.DfsTupleExtraction","spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.TargetActionEncoder","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"A single execution run of the PoC from start to finish must complete in\nless than 180 seconds on local CPU hardware.","hash":"bc623f401e61d6b915190e839e37637b50e332448ad368f76e00ebe9b956cb9b","inherits":["spec.rltree.ExecutionTimeConstraint","spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.ThreeMinuteBudget","type":"component"}
{"docstring":"At inference time, the model must output a valid SVG string that parses\nback to an XML element tree without raising exceptions.","hash":"a7d06e156682ffffe0df8b2cf4113d83b50c2e13967a83373fdfe6e86ea96cde","inherits":["spec.rltree.ExecutionTimeConstraint","spec.err.Err","spec.err.Refactor","spec.err.BoilerPlate","spec.err.FunctionLines","spec.err.Indentation","spec.err.Robustness","spec.err.PreCondition","spec.err.PostCondition","spec.err.GlobalMutableState","libspec.spec_types.Requirement"],"is_dependency":false,"is_template":false,"ref":"spec.rltree.ValidInferenceOutput","type":"component"}
